title: Cavaliers breeze by Delcastle, 41-6
text: Cavaliers breeze by Delcastle, 41-6 Comment By Mike Santa Barbara Posted Oct. 2, 2015 @ 10:49 pm The Middletown Cavaliers improved to 3-1 on the season, defeating Delcastle 41-6 on Friday night. The Cavaliers jumped on Delcastle wrapping up things early in some extremely windy and sometimes rainy conditions. Itâ€™s the sixth straight meeting between the two teams where Middletown has scored at least 40 points and kept Delcastle to eight points or less. The victory makes it two in a row for the Cavaliers who have now scored at least 35 points in each of their three wins this season. After a largely uneventful week four, Middletown goes back on the road next week traveling to Baynard Stadium to take on Salesianum Friday night at 7:30 p.m. Stay tuned for a preview of this big match up next week at middletowntranscript.com
